WEBVTT

00:34.380 --> 00:36.280
<i>- The designees are the ones</i>
<i>who are really in charge.</i>

00:36.480 --> 00:37.760
That's you.

00:37.960 --> 00:39.090
- It's next week.
It's a rally.

00:39.290 --> 00:40.890
<i>- What for?</i>
<i>- She's a witch.</i>

00:41.090 --> 00:42.590
- There's a crowd online
who are saying

00:42.790 --> 00:44.550
that the women were burned
for being like us.

00:44.750 --> 00:45.770
They are not like us.

00:45.970 --> 00:47.030
Let Sip go.

00:47.230 --> 00:49.340
Rowan!

00:49.540 --> 00:50.900
- Obey this man.
- He's the Witchfinder

00:51.100 --> 00:52.640
- of the king.
- She begged for blessin'

00:52.840 --> 00:53.990
from her dark lord,

00:54.190 --> 00:55.950
- a demon!
<i>- I'd be running.</i>

00:56.150 --> 00:58.000
- Those words are wicked.
Never speak them.

00:58.200 --> 00:59.080
What do you want from me?

00:59.280 --> 01:00.370
Only this.

01:00.570 --> 01:01.750
<i>[intense music]</i>

01:03.880 --> 01:07.190
[fire crackling]

01:15.290 --> 01:16.200
[knock at door]

01:22.600 --> 01:25.390
<i>[eerie music]</i>

01:25.590 --> 01:31.960
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:46.010 --> 01:46.970
No.

01:48.320 --> 01:49.800
<i>No!</i>

01:53.330 --> 01:55.110
[grunting]

01:58.200 --> 02:00.040
Never before

02:00.240 --> 02:02.930
have there been fewer men
in government,

02:03.130 --> 02:06.870
<i>in the media,</i>
<i>in our courts and factories,</i>

02:07.070 --> 02:09.810
<i>our military, our military!</i>

02:10.010 --> 02:15.770
And never before have we had
less control over our lives.

02:15.970 --> 02:20.640
<i>We have rolled over, given up,</i>
<i>drinkin' a beer,</i>

02:20.840 --> 02:24.100
<i>scrollin' our phones,</i>
<i>playin' a video game,</i>

02:24.300 --> 02:28.760
<i>ceding our livelihoods</i>
<i>and our dignity</i>

02:28.960 --> 02:31.830
<i>to a powerful cabal of women</i>

02:32.030 --> 02:34.720
<i>who have only just begun</i>

02:34.920 --> 02:40.710
<i>their slow and careful</i>
<i>overturning of our lives.</i>

02:40.910 --> 02:42.820
<i>You know who they are.</i>

02:43.020 --> 02:44.260
<i>And you know what they are.</i>

02:44.450 --> 02:45.580
<i>Go ahead, say it!</i>

02:45.780 --> 02:46.870
Witches.

02:47.070 --> 02:48.130
<i>- Say it!</i>
<i>crowd: Witches!</i>

02:48.330 --> 02:49.390
<i>- Say it!</i>
<i>crowd: Witches!</i>

02:49.590 --> 02:50.870
<i>- Say it!</i>
<i>crowd: Witches!</i>

02:51.070 --> 02:53.180
<i>That's right.</i>

02:53.380 --> 02:54.470
<i>Witches.</i>

02:55.560 --> 02:58.360
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:58.560 --> 03:05.350
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:08.840 --> 03:11.370
[wind gusting]

03:11.570 --> 03:14.090
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

03:14.290 --> 03:21.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:24.720 --> 03:26.250
Leave me alone.

03:26.450 --> 03:33.210
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:34.560 --> 03:37.220
Are you gone?

03:37.420 --> 03:43.740
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:46.870 --> 03:48.180
<i>I'm always with you.</i>

03:50.180 --> 03:51.700
<i>I'm a part of you...</i>

03:54.100 --> 03:55.480
<i>The part you pretend</i>
<i>not to see</i>

03:55.680 --> 03:57.760
<i>when you look</i>
<i>in the mirror.</i>

03:57.960 --> 04:00.720
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

04:00.920 --> 04:07.720
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:19.950 --> 04:21.260
<i>Is it good?</i>

04:23.430 --> 04:29.820
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:30.020 --> 04:31.820
<i>[laughs]</i>

04:32.020 --> 04:34.450
Fire can feel good too.

04:34.650 --> 04:38.240
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:38.440 --> 04:40.830
<i>See what happens</i>
<i>when you touch it.</i>

04:41.030 --> 04:47.880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:48.080 --> 04:49.860
<i>[gasps]</i>

04:50.060 --> 04:52.770
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

04:52.970 --> 04:59.770
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:02.380 --> 05:04.130
- It's not so hard to be happy,
is it?

05:04.330 --> 05:07.140
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:07.340 --> 05:08.610
[chuckles]

05:10.960 --> 05:11.790
<i>What are you doing?</i>

05:11.990 --> 05:13.310
[gasps]

05:15.660 --> 05:16.920
I got hungry.

05:20.580 --> 05:22.610
Was he here?

05:22.810 --> 05:25.630
- What?
- Was he here?

05:25.830 --> 05:27.160
No.

05:27.360 --> 05:28.550
- Well, why are you
wearing that?

05:28.750 --> 05:31.550
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:31.750 --> 05:34.360
Oh, I don't know.

05:34.560 --> 05:36.110
- You don't remember
putting it on?

05:37.510 --> 05:38.990
No.

05:39.190 --> 05:45.950
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:52.520 --> 05:54.010
He is here.

05:54.210 --> 05:57.880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:58.080 --> 05:59.650
I don't understand
how he's getting in

05:59.850 --> 06:01.710
<i>with all the protections</i>
<i>on this place.</i>

06:01.910 --> 06:03.280
Yeah, but the first night
you were here,

06:03.480 --> 06:04.980
he couldn't get in.

06:05.180 --> 06:07.590
He set that fire
to flush you out, so...

06:07.790 --> 06:10.070
[exhales sharply]

06:10.270 --> 06:11.550
<i>What's changed?</i>

06:11.750 --> 06:15.860
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:16.060 --> 06:17.470
The necklace.

06:17.670 --> 06:19.240
It's giving him access
to you somehow.

06:21.420 --> 06:24.280
Here. Let me take a look at it.

06:24.480 --> 06:31.260
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:35.870 --> 06:37.360
[sighs]

06:37.560 --> 06:40.510
It connects him to you,
obviously,

06:40.710 --> 06:42.400
but you were connected
before you put this on.

06:44.490 --> 06:48.580
So maybe it's some sort
of amplifier or conduit.

06:51.580 --> 06:53.130
I'll get it
out of the apartment.

06:53.330 --> 06:54.960
Then we'll see.

06:55.160 --> 06:57.490
I'll get it to the Talamasca.

06:57.690 --> 07:00.010
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:00.210 --> 07:01.800
No!

07:01.990 --> 07:03.190
- Give it to me!
- Ow, Rowan!

07:03.390 --> 07:05.170
Give it to me!

07:05.370 --> 07:07.040
<i>Don't come near me!</i>

07:07.240 --> 07:08.850
- It's mine! You can't have it!
- Okay.

07:09.040 --> 07:10.980
Stay away from me! It's mine!

07:11.180 --> 07:12.000
- All right.
- No, stay there!

07:12.200 --> 07:13.300
You can't have it!

07:14.430 --> 07:16.140
- It's mine!
<i>- Rowan.</i>

07:16.330 --> 07:18.140
It's mine.

07:18.340 --> 07:24.210
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:24.410 --> 07:26.140
He's in my head.

07:28.440 --> 07:29.800
He won't stop.

07:30.000 --> 07:32.390
He won't leave me alone.

07:32.590 --> 07:34.720
I'm sorry.

07:34.920 --> 07:36.850
It's okay.

07:37.050 --> 07:39.310
- [gasps] I--I lied.

07:39.510 --> 07:40.510
- I'm sorry I lied.
- It's okay.

07:40.710 --> 07:41.540
It's okay.

07:43.280 --> 07:44.550
Hey, look at me.

07:46.330 --> 07:49.020
- Okay?
- [breathing shakily]

07:49.220 --> 07:51.770
- Rowan.
- [mumbling indistinctly]

07:54.900 --> 07:56.220
- Okay?
- Yeah, yeah.

07:56.420 --> 07:57.460
- Okay?
- Here, take it.

07:57.660 --> 07:59.000
All right.

07:59.200 --> 08:01.180
[exhales heavily]

08:01.380 --> 08:02.480
All right, I'm goin'.

08:04.260 --> 08:06.030
And you be safe.

08:06.230 --> 08:09.010
<i>[somber music]</i>

08:09.210 --> 08:09.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:10.170 --> 08:11.390
You be safe.

08:11.590 --> 08:15.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:16.360 --> 08:19.500
<i>[eerie music]</i>

08:19.700 --> 08:22.220
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

08:22.420 --> 08:25.730
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:25.930 --> 08:29.400
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

08:29.600 --> 08:36.210
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:52.880 --> 08:54.700
- Hi.
- Hi. Come on in.

08:57.920 --> 08:59.040
[door bangs shut]

08:59.240 --> 09:01.280
Thanks for meeting me.

09:01.480 --> 09:03.130
Sure. What's going on?

09:03.330 --> 09:04.530
Here, sit.

09:04.730 --> 09:05.800
Oh, yeah.

09:09.720 --> 09:11.660
I have to show you something.

09:11.860 --> 09:12.810
<i>You okay?</i>

09:14.370 --> 09:15.930
Okay.

09:16.130 --> 09:17.690
- How are you so calm
about this?

09:17.890 --> 09:19.520
It--that's your mother's heart.

09:19.720 --> 09:21.110
- Well, I've seen a lot
of hearts.

09:21.310 --> 09:23.410
Who's NiteNite88?

09:23.610 --> 09:25.240
Do you want some coffee?

09:25.440 --> 09:27.960
- Sure.
- Yeah? Okay.

09:28.160 --> 09:30.140
- He's just this asshole
who's been DM'ing me.

09:30.340 --> 09:32.550
So I tracked him all the way
to a fringe imageboard,

09:32.750 --> 09:34.080
and it turns out,
there's a whole group of them

09:34.280 --> 09:35.540
posting about witches.

09:35.740 --> 09:36.880
- Are they the ones
burning women?

09:37.080 --> 09:39.170
I don't know. Uh, probably.

09:39.370 --> 09:41.350
I mean, not this guy.
He's just some local.

09:41.540 --> 09:42.800
But he--he's spreading it.

09:43.000 --> 09:45.150
And now he has Deirdre's heart.

09:45.350 --> 09:47.760
He--he's actually right.
He has a witch's heart.

09:49.850 --> 09:51.460
We have to do something.

09:52.760 --> 09:55.680
I mean, this is our family,
your family.

09:58.070 --> 10:00.910
I know it's probably different,

10:01.110 --> 10:02.950
coming into all of this
so suddenly.

10:04.860 --> 10:06.310
I mean, you got
to live your whole life

10:06.500 --> 10:08.830
thinking you were normal,
but you're not normal.

10:09.030 --> 10:10.590
<i>You're one of us.</i>

10:10.790 --> 10:13.250
<i>And we don't have the option</i>
<i>to walk away.</i>

10:13.450 --> 10:15.340
When they come for us,

10:15.540 --> 10:17.250
we have to stand together
and fight,

10:17.450 --> 10:18.800
or they'll destroy us.

10:19.000 --> 10:21.100
It's what they've been doing
for centuries.

10:21.300 --> 10:22.410
If this is that important,

10:22.610 --> 10:24.850
where's the rest of the family?

10:25.050 --> 10:28.390
- They don't take it
as seriously as they should.

10:28.590 --> 10:30.050
I thought maybe
you'd be different.

10:30.250 --> 10:31.920
Tessa, look.

10:32.120 --> 10:36.140
I admire your instinct
and conviction towards justice,

10:36.340 --> 10:37.820
but I'm not a vigilante.

10:38.010 --> 10:39.060
I don't--
I don't wanna get involved.

10:39.250 --> 10:40.540
- You got involved
with Carlotta.

10:40.730 --> 10:42.820
- That was different.
I was in danger.

10:43.020 --> 10:44.470
Okay. Sorry.

10:44.670 --> 10:47.560
- A heart is not a person.
It's a muscle.

10:47.760 --> 10:50.650
It's nothing worth risking
your safety over at all,

10:50.850 --> 10:52.420
under any circumstances.

10:52.620 --> 10:56.140
- The heart of the designee
is sacred to him.

10:56.340 --> 10:58.660
- You know how these guys
on the Internet

10:58.860 --> 10:59.920
are in your head
and you can't stop thinking

11:00.120 --> 11:01.100
about what they're saying?

11:01.300 --> 11:02.910
He's like that for me.

11:03.100 --> 11:05.150
He's trolling me.

11:05.350 --> 11:07.320
And I don't like it,
and I don't want it.

11:07.520 --> 11:09.320
Do you know what my power is?

11:09.520 --> 11:11.040
No.

11:11.240 --> 11:13.180
I have the power to glamour.

11:13.380 --> 11:15.110
<i>My awesome witch power</i>

11:15.310 --> 11:17.720
is that I can put a man
under a trance

11:17.920 --> 11:20.490
for a few minutes
so they can't think straight.

11:20.690 --> 11:22.450
[laughing] I mean,
what kind of power is that?

11:22.650 --> 11:26.170
But you, you have real power
right at your fingertips,

11:26.370 --> 11:27.520
and--and you're doing
everything you can

11:27.720 --> 11:29.110
not to use it.

11:29.300 --> 11:31.560
- Because there's a price
with him.

11:31.760 --> 11:33.070
I don't want his power.

11:33.270 --> 11:35.200
I want my own power
on my own terms.

11:35.400 --> 11:36.400
Do you understand that?

11:36.590 --> 11:38.880
<i>Tessa, listen.</i>

11:39.080 --> 11:43.690
My advice to you is,
don't feed the trolls.

11:43.880 --> 11:45.700
Just go live your life.

11:48.050 --> 11:49.390
- Maybe you should go
do the same.

11:49.590 --> 11:51.260
I wish I could, believe me.

11:51.460 --> 11:52.670
I--I wish I could,
but that's just--

11:52.870 --> 11:53.930
that's just not possible
anymore.

11:54.130 --> 11:56.070
Are you sure?

11:56.270 --> 11:58.070
Or is that something
he wants you to believe?

11:58.270 --> 12:02.180
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:02.380 --> 12:04.380
<i>- Rowan Fielding is here</i>
<i>to see you.</i>

12:04.580 --> 12:06.240
Ah. Oh.

12:07.850 --> 12:11.450
Well, what a nice surprise.

12:11.650 --> 12:12.670
How are you settlin'
in the house?

12:12.870 --> 12:13.780
Oh, I'm not.

12:13.980 --> 12:15.850
I won't be.

12:16.050 --> 12:18.660
- Well, it's been ours
since we came from Haiti.

12:18.850 --> 12:20.960
I can't imagine it
sittin' there empty.

12:21.160 --> 12:22.330
Do you want it?

12:22.530 --> 12:24.100
I'd sell it to you
for a dollar.

12:24.290 --> 12:27.360
- [chuckles]
Well, I can't let you do that.

12:27.560 --> 12:29.230
That's just bad business.
[laughs]

12:29.430 --> 12:30.990
<i>Hmm.</i>

12:31.190 --> 12:32.360
I can see there's mud
in your pump.

12:32.560 --> 12:33.450
Here, sit down.
Have some tea.

12:33.650 --> 12:35.710
Uh, tell me all about it.

12:45.930 --> 12:47.730
[sighs]

12:47.930 --> 12:49.990
You're just not used
to him is all.

12:50.190 --> 12:51.800
<i>As soon as you settle</i>
<i>into your new role,</i>

12:52.000 --> 12:53.860
I know you'll find him useful.

12:54.060 --> 12:55.610
No, I want him gone.

12:55.800 --> 12:57.500
[scoffs]

12:57.700 --> 12:59.910
Now, he spooked you, didn't he?

13:00.110 --> 13:02.090
The--the--the incident
with Carlotta.

13:02.290 --> 13:05.270
- Why does everyone assume
they know what happened?

13:05.470 --> 13:07.160
Well, are we wrong?

13:07.360 --> 13:10.380
- Here. Sugar?
- No. Thank you.

13:10.580 --> 13:12.600
<i>- Now, I understand</i>
<i>how that would be upsetting.</i>

13:12.800 --> 13:15.450
But you don't have anything
to be afraid of.

13:15.650 --> 13:17.170
Take the reins.
Tell him what you want.

13:17.370 --> 13:18.580
He's part of you.

13:18.780 --> 13:21.070
No, I want that part cut out.

13:21.260 --> 13:24.460
Well, um,

13:24.660 --> 13:27.060
I wish I could help,
but it's impossible.

13:30.850 --> 13:34.470
<i>[eerie music]</i>

13:34.670 --> 13:36.290
[sighs]

13:44.560 --> 13:46.650
How long have you known?

13:47.730 --> 13:49.480
Known what, <i>cher?</i>

13:49.680 --> 13:51.530
And your--
your tea's gettin' cold.

13:51.730 --> 13:53.860
The ALS.

13:54.060 --> 13:55.830
How long
since it was diagnosed?

14:02.140 --> 14:04.020
<i>[sighs]</i>

14:04.220 --> 14:05.490
You mustn't tell anyone.

14:08.190 --> 14:11.540
Jojo in particular
would not take it well.

14:13.150 --> 14:15.400
- Everybody's gonna find out
soon enough.

14:15.600 --> 14:17.400
Your lung function
is very impaired.

14:17.600 --> 14:19.200
Have you started cell therapy?

14:20.720 --> 14:22.280
[sighs] Yeah.

14:22.480 --> 14:23.870
Last week.

14:24.070 --> 14:25.340
That's good.

14:26.990 --> 14:29.340
There are a number
of new treatments.

14:32.430 --> 14:34.400
If you want me to consult
with your doctor

14:34.600 --> 14:36.740
and review your treatment plan,
I'd be happy to.

14:38.440 --> 14:39.480
Thank you.

14:40.920 --> 14:43.500
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:43.690 --> 14:45.350
- If you knew there was a way
for me to remove the disease

14:45.540 --> 14:48.000
from your body completely,

14:48.200 --> 14:50.520
you would want me to do it,
wouldn't you?

14:50.720 --> 14:51.870
Of course.

14:52.070 --> 14:55.090
That's exactly how I feel.

14:55.290 --> 14:58.600
I want my own self back.

14:58.800 --> 15:00.770
So why won't you help me?

15:00.970 --> 15:03.170
[chuckles]

15:03.370 --> 15:05.900
Oh, he can't be gotten rid of.

15:07.600 --> 15:08.550
[sighs]

15:10.560 --> 15:14.110
But a transfer
was performed once

15:14.310 --> 15:16.050
for Katherine Mayfair

15:16.250 --> 15:18.970
<i>to her brother,</i>
<i>my father, Julien.</i>

15:19.170 --> 15:20.840
How do we do it?

15:21.040 --> 15:23.270
- Uh, I wouldn't know
where to start.

15:23.470 --> 15:27.100
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:27.300 --> 15:30.520
But my cousin Dolly Jean
might know.

15:30.720 --> 15:31.780
I can talk to her.

15:31.980 --> 15:35.200
Please, yes. Yes. Thank you.

15:35.400 --> 15:36.580
Now, I have an idea.

15:38.370 --> 15:40.750
I wonder
if you could help me out.

15:40.950 --> 15:44.030
You know, we run the Mayfair
wing at NOLA Medical.

15:44.230 --> 15:45.580
Would you do a walk-through
with Jojo?

15:45.780 --> 15:47.230
She's on the board,
and we're doing a review

15:47.430 --> 15:49.450
of our care model.

15:49.650 --> 15:52.780
I would love
your expert opinion.

15:52.980 --> 15:55.420
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:55.610 --> 15:57.530
- I'm sure there are
many experts here.

15:57.730 --> 16:01.180
- And you're asking me
to do a favor for you, <i>cher.</i>

16:01.380 --> 16:04.320
I mean, surely you'll grant me
the same courtesy.

16:04.510 --> 16:06.660
Now, you come from a long line
of healers.

16:08.310 --> 16:11.320
And you're makin'
'em all proud.

16:11.520 --> 16:14.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:14.310 --> 16:15.740
- If I can understand
how the connection

16:15.940 --> 16:17.980
between Lasher
and the family began,

16:18.180 --> 16:19.830
then I have a better chance
of ending it.

16:20.030 --> 16:21.900
- But it's a magical object,
Ciprien.

16:22.100 --> 16:23.290
<i>There's no way to predict</i>
<i>what will happen</i>

16:23.490 --> 16:24.640
<i>when you connect with it.</i>

16:24.840 --> 16:26.290
<i>It could be very different.</i>

16:26.490 --> 16:28.380
I can't promise
to keep you safe.

16:28.580 --> 16:30.820
- No, but I'll feel much better
with you watching me.

16:31.020 --> 16:33.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:33.390 --> 16:35.150
- We should take this
to the mother house.

16:35.350 --> 16:36.630
We need real guidance.

16:36.830 --> 16:38.120
There's no time for that.

16:39.990 --> 16:41.170
You ready?

16:43.430 --> 16:46.840
You can stay here with me,
or I can do it alone.

16:47.040 --> 16:53.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:03.370 --> 17:06.030
<i>[dramatic percussive music]</i>

17:06.230 --> 17:07.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:07.580 --> 17:08.720
Oh, no.

17:29.480 --> 17:31.880
<i>She helped Marcus.</i>

17:32.080 --> 17:33.050
<i>- Aye, aye,</i>
<i>Suzanne helped me.</i>

17:39.270 --> 17:40.230
<i>No.</i>

18:02.380 --> 18:04.260
- [grunts]
- [gasps, moans]

18:04.460 --> 18:06.960
[crowd gasps]

18:07.160 --> 18:09.780
- [yells]
- [grunting]

18:14.130 --> 18:15.860
[crowd clamoring]

18:16.060 --> 18:18.100
<i>No! No!</i>

18:18.300 --> 18:19.970
No! No!

18:20.170 --> 18:22.100
<i>No! No!</i>

18:25.450 --> 18:27.480
- Isn't this a little early,
even for you?

18:27.680 --> 18:29.940
<i>[tense music]</i>

18:30.140 --> 18:32.200
You could blame her.

18:32.400 --> 18:33.380
She's driven me to it.

18:33.580 --> 18:36.790
She has and quickly.

18:36.990 --> 18:38.860
I can't fathom
for the life of me

18:39.060 --> 18:41.250
<i>why you think</i>
<i>we should capitulate to this.</i>

18:42.680 --> 18:46.370
- We can't exactly force her
to behave like a designee.

18:46.570 --> 18:48.520
Have you tried?

18:48.720 --> 18:51.000
- After 30 years of Carlotta
strangling the power

18:51.200 --> 18:53.940
out of the designee,

18:54.140 --> 18:56.440
we need someone to lead us
who believes in this family.

18:56.640 --> 18:58.770
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:58.970 --> 19:01.380
Uh, Rowan, uh,
raised out of the nest,

19:01.580 --> 19:04.140
so perhaps it's too much
to ask her to change.

19:05.620 --> 19:06.800
But will he change?

19:07.000 --> 19:08.590
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:08.790 --> 19:09.840
[chuckles]

19:11.620 --> 19:13.420
He might.

19:13.620 --> 19:15.200
And if he doesn't,

19:15.400 --> 19:16.460
so be it.

19:16.660 --> 19:21.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:21.540 --> 19:24.210
I did find something

19:24.410 --> 19:25.470
in your father's diary.

19:25.670 --> 19:32.470
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:37.170 --> 19:39.200
- Oh--

19:39.400 --> 19:41.530
she'll be taking a risk.

19:41.730 --> 19:43.270
- Perhaps warning her
would be enough

19:43.470 --> 19:45.360
to get her to change her mind.

19:45.560 --> 19:47.520
- You think it's still
in the house?

19:47.720 --> 19:49.180
I know where to look.

19:50.710 --> 19:52.720
<i>Uh, one hiccup.</i>

19:52.920 --> 19:54.830
For this to work,

19:55.030 --> 19:58.980
the family's going
to need Deirdre's blessing.

19:59.180 --> 20:02.920
And how we get that,
only heaven knows.

20:03.120 --> 20:05.860
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:06.060 --> 20:08.040
I'll call him.

20:08.240 --> 20:15.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:15.480 --> 20:16.910
<i>But don't give me</i>
<i>too much credit.</i>

20:18.560 --> 20:21.090
I was just being sentimental.

20:21.290 --> 20:22.830
<i>We are fully dedicated</i>

20:23.030 --> 20:25.250
to becoming
a world-class institution,

20:25.450 --> 20:27.600
and that includes
actively searching

20:27.800 --> 20:30.410
for a new chief
of neurosurgery.

20:30.610 --> 20:34.000
- I'm very flattered,
but San Francisco's my home.

20:34.200 --> 20:35.650
- [sighs]
Is it, though?

20:35.850 --> 20:37.810
I mean, what's--
what's there for you?

20:38.010 --> 20:39.630
My job, for one.

20:39.830 --> 20:42.580
- Sure, but at this job,
you'd be your own boss.

20:44.460 --> 20:45.470
Okay, may I at least
tell my dad

20:45.670 --> 20:47.120
you're thinking about it?

20:47.320 --> 20:48.450
- You can tell your dad
whatever you want.

20:48.650 --> 20:50.580
<i>[dramatic musical sting]</i>

20:50.780 --> 20:52.930
What's down this way?

20:53.130 --> 20:54.610
Is everything okay?

20:54.800 --> 20:57.560
<i>[eerie music]</i>

20:57.760 --> 20:59.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:00.050 --> 21:01.210
Not really.

21:03.080 --> 21:04.330
He won't leave me alone.

21:04.530 --> 21:06.030
- I wish I knew
how to help you.

21:06.230 --> 21:07.470
God, there are people
in our family

21:07.670 --> 21:09.090
who would kill
to have him.

21:10.390 --> 21:12.650
I don't mean that literally.

21:12.840 --> 21:14.320
Are you sure?

21:14.520 --> 21:17.320
<i>[ominous music]</i>

21:17.520 --> 21:18.870
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:19.070 --> 21:20.910
Jojo?

21:21.110 --> 21:22.180
[exhales heavily]

21:22.380 --> 21:23.760
Are you okay?

21:23.960 --> 21:26.420
Uh, I'm sorry.

21:26.620 --> 21:31.100
I have visions sometimes,
uh, premonitions.

21:31.300 --> 21:34.170
- Oh, wow.
What did you just see?

21:34.370 --> 21:35.820
- I need to take you
to the house to meet someone.

21:36.020 --> 21:38.000
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:38.200 --> 21:39.780
She's here.

21:39.980 --> 21:46.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:50.570 --> 21:52.860
Thank you, darlin'.

21:53.060 --> 21:54.950
- Thank you so much
for doing this for me.

21:55.150 --> 21:56.800
Don't thank me yet.

21:57.000 --> 22:03.800
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:18.070 --> 22:20.060
<i>This way, dear.</i>
<i>Come and talk with us.</i>

22:20.260 --> 22:22.390
- I'll be right in.
Just one--one minute.

22:22.590 --> 22:25.350
<i>[eerie music]</i>

22:25.550 --> 22:30.220
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:30.420 --> 22:33.530
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

22:33.730 --> 22:40.430
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:40.630 --> 22:42.190
[sighs]

22:42.390 --> 22:47.410
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:47.610 --> 22:48.700
[sighs]

22:48.900 --> 22:50.590
The object of the ceremony

22:50.790 --> 22:54.810
is to transfer the power
to a female next of kin.

22:55.010 --> 22:57.180
- Okay.
- Are they comin'?

22:57.380 --> 22:59.560
- They'll be here,
the ones who matter.

22:59.760 --> 23:01.040
They all need to come.

23:01.240 --> 23:02.510
They all matter.

23:06.860 --> 23:08.850
And you will also need
to do your part.

23:09.050 --> 23:10.870
Whatever it takes.

23:11.070 --> 23:14.380
- That's well put,
because it may take something.

23:14.570 --> 23:16.380
What do you mean?

23:16.580 --> 23:19.080
- Lasher is connected
to our family's bloodline,

23:19.270 --> 23:21.820
to your matrilineal bloodline,

23:22.020 --> 23:23.380
<i>the blood that's been flowin'</i>
<i>through your veins</i>

23:23.580 --> 23:25.650
<i>since you were conceived.</i>

23:25.850 --> 23:29.000
A connection to him has always
been there inside you,

23:29.200 --> 23:30.940
dormant.

23:31.130 --> 23:32.890
<i>If we're successful</i>
<i>and he leaves you,</i>

23:33.090 --> 23:34.740
you may suffer other losses
as well.

23:34.940 --> 23:36.480
Other losses like what?

23:36.680 --> 23:38.720
- I hear you have
a medical intuition.

23:40.280 --> 23:42.510
Like many doctors, I do, yes.

23:42.710 --> 23:44.060
- You don't believe
your gifts have helped you

23:44.260 --> 23:45.430
in your profession?

23:45.630 --> 23:46.950
- Are you saying
that without Lasher,

23:47.150 --> 23:48.760
I'll lose ten years
of medical experience

23:48.960 --> 23:50.390
and my board certification?

23:50.590 --> 23:51.890
Bear with me, sweetheart.

23:52.090 --> 23:54.050
I'm not trying
to set your teeth on edge.

23:54.240 --> 23:57.130
But you need to know the risks
before you commit to this.

23:57.950 --> 23:59.990
- My ability as a surgeon
is my own.

24:00.190 --> 24:01.570
It has nothing to do with him.

24:01.770 --> 24:03.530
- Everyone who walks
into that room today

24:03.730 --> 24:05.800
is taking on risk.

24:06.000 --> 24:07.990
<i>They all know that,</i>
<i>and so should you.</i>

24:08.190 --> 24:10.280
How it goes is down to him

24:10.480 --> 24:12.880
and how he responds
to your request.

24:15.270 --> 24:16.540
Is it worth it, Rowan?

24:18.970 --> 24:21.890
- Who will he go to
if this works?

24:25.810 --> 24:28.170
That, I don't know.

24:28.370 --> 24:30.810
She must choose him,
and he must choose her.

24:34.340 --> 24:37.340
[door creaking]

24:41.430 --> 24:45.050
Must be 50 years
since anyone's been in here.

24:45.250 --> 24:47.970
<i>Carlotta locked the door</i>
<i>and threw away her key.</i>

24:48.170 --> 24:49.410
- She didn't clean
anything out.

24:49.600 --> 24:51.730
I imagine she tried

24:51.930 --> 24:55.890
and was met
with some...resistance.

24:56.090 --> 25:00.050
This was her father's workshop,
and he left it protected.

25:00.250 --> 25:02.220
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:02.420 --> 25:04.830
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

25:05.030 --> 25:06.860
Was he a doctor too?

25:07.060 --> 25:10.820
- A banker with a penchant
for necromancy.

25:11.020 --> 25:17.820
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:19.990 --> 25:22.180
<i>There it is.</i>

25:22.380 --> 25:24.180
Get this for me,
would you, dear?

25:24.380 --> 25:31.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:36.360 --> 25:37.710
Well, open it.

25:37.910 --> 25:44.710
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:45.190 --> 25:49.270
[sighs]

25:49.470 --> 25:53.730
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:53.930 --> 25:55.860
Bring her out.

25:56.060 --> 26:02.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:03.030 --> 26:04.560
Whose bones are these?

26:06.040 --> 26:07.520
Everyone's.

26:09.480 --> 26:13.950
She was assembled with parts
from all the designees.

26:14.150 --> 26:17.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:17.540 --> 26:20.180
She's their tangible presence
in this world.

26:22.100 --> 26:23.240
Stella's teeth,

26:23.440 --> 26:26.350
Mary Beth's fingernails.

26:26.550 --> 26:29.060
<i>Her head</i>
<i>is Deborah's hip bone.</i>

26:30.980 --> 26:34.250
<i>The body of the designee</i>
<i>is sacred to the man.</i>

26:34.450 --> 26:36.600
That's why Julien used her
in his ceremony,

26:36.800 --> 26:40.150
and that's why we're using her
tonight.

26:40.350 --> 26:42.130
To do something
of this magnitude,

26:42.330 --> 26:44.650
we need their blessing.

26:44.850 --> 26:46.030
You understand?

26:48.080 --> 26:49.350
Yes.

26:49.550 --> 26:51.310
Now, here's the final piece.

26:51.510 --> 26:57.950
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:58.150 --> 26:59.620
Cut from your mother's head.

26:59.820 --> 27:01.930
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:02.130 --> 27:03.390
<i>Go on, now.</i>

27:03.590 --> 27:05.450
Braid it in.

27:05.650 --> 27:08.040
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:08.240 --> 27:10.000
Sweetheart,
if you want this to work,

27:10.200 --> 27:12.810
you need
to behave like a Mayfair.

27:13.010 --> 27:15.010
If you let your rational mind
get in the way,

27:15.210 --> 27:17.890
we may as well stop right now.

27:19.850 --> 27:21.640
Okay, braid it in.

27:21.840 --> 27:23.120
- Mm-hmm.

27:23.320 --> 27:26.650
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:26.850 --> 27:28.150
<i>Braid it in.</i>

27:28.350 --> 27:29.960
- Like this?
<i>- Mm-hmm.</i>

27:30.160 --> 27:35.050
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:35.250 --> 27:36.810
<i>- They say fire's</i>
<i>a horrible way to die.</i>

27:37.010 --> 27:38.310
- That's right.
- Yeah.

27:38.510 --> 27:39.950
<i>- So let's talk</i>
<i>about this woman,</i>

27:40.140 --> 27:42.470
<i>Polly Jenkins,</i>
<i>an entrepreneur from Memphis</i>

27:42.670 --> 27:45.540
<i>burned alive yesterday</i>
<i>with a stack of garbage.</i>

27:45.740 --> 27:47.080
<i>Now, if you listen</i>
<i>to the media,</i>

27:47.280 --> 27:49.080
<i>they will tell you</i>
<i>that she was a victim.</i>

27:49.280 --> 27:52.130
But a victim is someone who has
something done to them, yes?

27:52.330 --> 27:53.890
- Yes.
- Yep.

27:54.090 --> 27:56.830
- Nobody made Polly Jenkins
practice witchcraft.

27:57.030 --> 27:58.310
- No.
- In fact,

27:58.510 --> 28:00.360
you can read her testimony.

28:00.560 --> 28:04.640
On her own website, she says
that she lost her faith

28:04.840 --> 28:07.040
<i>in the values</i>
<i>of the Christian church</i>

28:07.240 --> 28:09.760
<i>and she found them</i>
<i>in sisterhood.</i>

28:09.960 --> 28:11.110
- Shame!
- Ooh!

28:11.310 --> 28:12.410
- She also talks
about a network

28:12.610 --> 28:15.220
of women empowering each other.

28:15.420 --> 28:17.590
She pretty much spells it out
right there, folks.

28:17.790 --> 28:20.220
There are women in this country

28:20.420 --> 28:21.770
who have made a deal
with the devil

28:21.970 --> 28:23.550
<i>to have it all,</i>

28:23.750 --> 28:26.030
and Polly Jenkins
was one of them.

28:26.230 --> 28:27.100
- Yeah!
- That's right!

28:27.300 --> 28:28.360
<i>She is not a victim.</i>

28:28.560 --> 28:30.060
No.

28:30.260 --> 28:33.450
- And I am here today
to tell you

28:33.650 --> 28:36.240
<i>that women like Polly Jenkins</i>
<i>are hoping</i>

28:36.440 --> 28:38.570
<i>that we will just stand back</i>
<i>and watch</i>

28:38.770 --> 28:40.200
<i>while they take control</i>

28:40.400 --> 28:42.160
<i>not just of the places</i>
<i>where we live</i>

28:42.360 --> 28:44.120
<i>and work and worship</i>

28:44.320 --> 28:45.580
but our government.

28:45.780 --> 28:47.470
- No way!
- And our military!

28:47.670 --> 28:50.040
- No!
- And you.

28:50.240 --> 28:52.800
You are here today
because you know

28:53.000 --> 28:54.650
<i>that these women</i>
<i>are not victims</i>

28:54.850 --> 28:57.480
and because you are not
willing to cede control

28:57.680 --> 28:59.370
- of your lives.
- No way!

28:59.570 --> 29:00.530
You're going to fight.

29:00.720 --> 29:02.220
- Yeah!
<i>- Aren't you?</i>

29:02.420 --> 29:04.790
You're gonna make sure
that any woman

29:04.990 --> 29:07.160
that makes a deal
with the devil gets burned!

29:07.360 --> 29:09.100
[crowd cheering]

29:09.300 --> 29:10.840
Fire!

29:11.040 --> 29:12.410
[cheers and applause]

29:12.610 --> 29:13.470
Yes.

29:13.670 --> 29:15.080
<i>To the river!</i>

29:15.280 --> 29:16.920
<i>- Aye!</i>
- [growls]

29:21.760 --> 29:23.280
No.

29:24.800 --> 29:26.410
Aye. Aye.

29:28.370 --> 29:29.900
<i>Let's go, witch!</i>

29:30.100 --> 29:32.200
[panting]

29:33.810 --> 29:36.120
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

29:41.470 --> 29:42.980
<i>Have mercy!</i>

29:43.180 --> 29:44.530
<i>I've done no wrong!</i>

29:44.730 --> 29:47.070
<i>I've done no wrong!</i>

29:47.270 --> 29:49.550
<i>all:</i>
<i>Suzanne.</i>

29:49.750 --> 29:51.380
Deborah.

29:51.580 --> 29:52.560
Charlotte.

29:52.750 --> 29:54.800
Jeanne-Louise.

29:55.000 --> 29:56.450
Angelique.

29:56.650 --> 29:58.610
Marie Claudette.

29:58.800 --> 30:00.150
Marguerite.

30:00.350 --> 30:01.740
Julien.

30:01.940 --> 30:03.460
Mary Beth.

30:03.660 --> 30:04.920
Stella.

30:05.120 --> 30:06.400
Antha.

30:06.590 --> 30:08.220
Deirdre.

30:08.420 --> 30:10.010
Rowan.

30:10.210 --> 30:12.660
- Suzanne.
- Now the doll.

30:12.860 --> 30:15.470
<i>[dramatic percussive music]</i>

30:15.670 --> 30:19.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:19.740 --> 30:22.540
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

30:22.740 --> 30:29.520
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:31.830 --> 30:33.710
<i>Ancestors,</i>

30:33.900 --> 30:35.660
<i>mothers of our mothers,</i>

30:35.860 --> 30:38.820
bearers of our coven,

30:39.020 --> 30:40.800
on this night, we ask

30:41.000 --> 30:43.240
<i>that you give us</i>
<i>your blessing.</i>

30:43.440 --> 30:46.390
<i>Honor our appeal.</i>

30:46.590 --> 30:49.200
<i>Welcome Lasher into this room</i>

30:49.400 --> 30:52.380
<i>so that he may be bound</i>
<i>to another witch.</i>

30:52.580 --> 30:54.360
We beseech you.

30:54.560 --> 30:56.230
<i>Grant us this request.</i>

30:56.430 --> 30:58.670
<i>We beseech you.</i>

30:58.860 --> 31:01.210
<i>Grant us this request.</i>

31:01.410 --> 31:03.710
<i>We beseech you.</i>

31:03.910 --> 31:06.590
Grant us this request.

31:06.790 --> 31:13.590
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:13.790 --> 31:16.880
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

31:17.080 --> 31:23.880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:39.110 --> 31:40.880
- In your family
who you suspect of witchcraft,

31:41.080 --> 31:42.160
you have to report it.

31:43.590 --> 31:44.770
Great speech.

31:47.200 --> 31:49.410
Thank you, brother.

31:49.610 --> 31:50.870
<i>The other thing, too,</i>
<i>is that if you see something,</i>

31:51.070 --> 31:51.940
<i>you need to take</i>
<i>your camera out.</i>

31:52.140 --> 31:53.340
You heard about the Mayfairs?

31:55.780 --> 31:57.120
Right? I mean,
you've heard the rumors?

31:57.310 --> 31:59.260
- Who are you?
- I'm Keith Murfis.

32:00.910 --> 32:02.000
How you doin', Keith?

32:03.260 --> 32:05.040
Here.

32:05.240 --> 32:06.350
Look at this.

32:09.440 --> 32:12.830
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:13.030 --> 32:15.710
That's Deirdre Mayfair's heart.

32:17.580 --> 32:18.710
How did you get this?

32:20.410 --> 32:21.600
Work in the morgue.

32:21.800 --> 32:25.950
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:26.150 --> 32:27.950
Folks!

32:28.150 --> 32:29.600
Look at this.

32:29.800 --> 32:33.430
I have in my hands
the heart of a witch!

32:33.630 --> 32:34.980
[cheers and applause]

32:35.180 --> 32:36.130
Come get a good look.

32:36.330 --> 32:39.240
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:39.440 --> 32:40.400
All right.

32:40.600 --> 32:42.490
[indistinct chatter]

32:42.690 --> 32:45.230
[crowd clamoring]

32:45.430 --> 32:46.740
<i>Sister!</i>

32:48.660 --> 32:49.930
Oh, no.

32:50.130 --> 32:51.970
<i>[gasping]</i>

33:00.280 --> 33:02.530
No!

33:02.730 --> 33:05.670
[crowd clamoring]

33:11.680 --> 33:13.320
[crying]

33:13.520 --> 33:14.870
crowd: Witch! Witch!

33:15.070 --> 33:16.520
<i>Use the wicked words!</i>

33:16.720 --> 33:18.500
crowd: Witch! Witch!

33:18.700 --> 33:20.300
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

33:22.650 --> 33:24.430
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

33:28.650 --> 33:31.580
<i>- Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

33:31.780 --> 33:33.820
Mi Daemon, ad me veni.

33:34.020 --> 33:35.870
Mi Daemon, mihi labora.

33:36.070 --> 33:38.060
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

33:38.260 --> 33:40.000
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

33:40.200 --> 33:42.350
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

33:42.550 --> 33:45.030
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

33:45.230 --> 33:46.660
[people screaming]
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

33:46.860 --> 33:48.660
<i>- He's still yours.</i>
<i>You need to call him.</i>

33:48.860 --> 33:50.550
Use the words I taught you.

33:51.890 --> 33:54.080
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

33:54.280 --> 33:56.080
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

33:56.280 --> 33:57.390
Like you mean it.

33:57.590 --> 33:58.910
Call him.

33:59.110 --> 34:02.890
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

34:03.090 --> 34:06.530
Mi Daemon, ad me veni.

34:06.730 --> 34:08.860
- <i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>
- Y'all help her.

34:09.050 --> 34:13.250
all: <i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

34:13.450 --> 34:16.230
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

34:16.430 --> 34:17.970
Louder!

34:18.170 --> 34:20.610
all: <i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

34:20.810 --> 34:24.110
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

34:24.310 --> 34:27.550
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

34:27.750 --> 34:31.570
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

34:31.770 --> 34:34.160
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

34:34.360 --> 34:35.880
- Something's happening.
<i>- Mi Daemon...</i>

34:36.080 --> 34:37.540
I feel it!

34:37.740 --> 34:38.890
[shrieks]

34:39.080 --> 34:40.950
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

34:41.150 --> 34:43.300
Mi Daemon, mihi labora.

34:43.500 --> 34:45.760
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

34:45.960 --> 34:48.290
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

34:48.490 --> 34:50.960
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

34:51.160 --> 34:52.590
Mi Daemon, mihi labora.

34:52.790 --> 34:54.220
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

34:58.000 --> 34:58.920
<i>- Mi Daemon, ad me--</i>

35:00.790 --> 35:02.440
[people screaming]

35:09.360 --> 35:11.500
He's coming. Keep going!

35:11.700 --> 35:14.570
<i>- Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

35:14.770 --> 35:17.640
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

35:17.840 --> 35:19.930
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

35:20.130 --> 35:22.970
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

35:23.170 --> 35:24.640
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

35:33.260 --> 35:36.120
[breathing heavily]

35:36.320 --> 35:38.620
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

35:38.820 --> 35:40.230
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:40.430 --> 35:43.320
All of this to be rid of me.

35:43.520 --> 35:49.800
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:50.000 --> 35:51.010
Yes.

35:54.230 --> 35:55.630
But look at you.

35:58.500 --> 36:01.470
After years
of hiding who you are,

36:01.670 --> 36:03.500
you're finally uncovering
your true self.

36:05.770 --> 36:07.160
Why would you forsake her?

36:09.810 --> 36:11.830
I can be myself without you.

36:12.030 --> 36:18.820
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:21.130 --> 36:22.780
- There are risks
to what you're doing.

36:24.130 --> 36:25.530
You understand them?

36:27.880 --> 36:29.260
I do.

36:29.460 --> 36:34.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:35.050 --> 36:37.070
[breathing shallowly]

36:37.270 --> 36:44.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:50.860 --> 36:53.470
[breathing shallowly]

36:55.210 --> 36:58.050
[gasping]

36:58.250 --> 37:05.040
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:05.870 --> 37:07.220
[gasps]

37:10.310 --> 37:13.000
[coughs]

37:13.190 --> 37:14.820
- [gags]
- Wait.

37:15.020 --> 37:16.410
[coughs]

37:16.610 --> 37:19.480
[choking]

37:19.680 --> 37:22.440
<i>[tense music]</i>

37:22.640 --> 37:29.290
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:29.490 --> 37:30.940
[gasps]

37:36.600 --> 37:43.430
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:44.560 --> 37:48.270
<i>[panting]</i>

37:48.470 --> 37:55.270
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:16.030 --> 38:17.070
Shall I?

38:18.680 --> 38:20.480
Be brave.

38:20.680 --> 38:22.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:22.370 --> 38:23.610
Tessa, no.

38:23.810 --> 38:30.570
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:30.770 --> 38:33.490
[breathing heavily]

38:33.690 --> 38:40.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:41.230 --> 38:43.620
He has chosen.

38:44.880 --> 38:46.010
<i>[chuckles]</i>

38:48.320 --> 38:51.160
[both chuckle]

38:51.360 --> 38:54.840
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:55.040 --> 38:57.710
<i>Oh, congratulations.</i>

38:57.910 --> 39:00.780
<i>[indistinct chatter]</i>

39:00.980 --> 39:03.870
<i>- Well done.</i>
<i>- You did it.</i>

39:04.070 --> 39:06.030
<i>Ah. Oh, my dear.</i>

39:11.080 --> 39:12.520
And?

39:17.650 --> 39:19.790
- Can you still see?
- Yes.

39:21.920 --> 39:23.880
It wasn't him.
It was always me.

39:25.580 --> 39:26.910
I'm fine.

39:27.110 --> 39:29.980
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

39:30.180 --> 39:32.420
Then why do you look so sad?

39:32.620 --> 39:35.380
<i>[somber music]</i>

39:35.580 --> 39:39.030
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:39.230 --> 39:42.560
[fire roaring]

39:42.760 --> 39:49.560
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:57.610 --> 39:59.270
[groans]

39:59.470 --> 40:06.010
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:13.750 --> 40:14.710
[growls]

40:15.670 --> 40:17.540
[groans]

40:19.240 --> 40:22.120
[choking]

40:22.320 --> 40:29.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:50.090 --> 40:56.930
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:15.990 --> 41:18.960
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:19.160 --> 41:22.770
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:22.970 --> 41:24.650
- Something has happened.
Your mind races.

41:36.400 --> 41:38.170
Sip.

41:38.370 --> 41:39.840
The necklace is gone.

41:42.060 --> 41:45.020
You must find your own way
out of the memory.

41:47.890 --> 41:50.710
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

41:50.910 --> 41:57.680
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:12.790 --> 42:14.190
Whenever you're ready,

42:14.390 --> 42:16.690
here I am.

42:16.890 --> 42:19.350
<i>Tessa! Come downstairs!</i>

42:19.540 --> 42:21.240
<i>We're gonna celebrate!</i>

42:21.440 --> 42:27.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:49.210 --> 42:52.100
[fire roaring]

42:52.290 --> 42:57.090
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:16.410 --> 43:23.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:25.340 --> 43:28.470
[insects chirping]

43:36.740 --> 43:37.780
[twig snaps]

43:45.790 --> 43:46.750
Hey.

43:48.620 --> 43:50.260
- Hi.
- Here you are.

43:50.460 --> 43:51.890
[chuckles]

43:52.090 --> 43:53.940
NiteNite88, right?

43:54.140 --> 43:55.790
Yeah.

43:55.990 --> 43:57.470
Did you bring it?

43:57.660 --> 43:58.620
Yeah.

43:58.820 --> 43:59.940
Oh, it's in there.

44:01.900 --> 44:03.490
Wow.

44:03.690 --> 44:06.820
That's, uh, really cool.

44:07.020 --> 44:08.280
Thanks.

44:08.480 --> 44:09.650
How'd you get it?

44:09.850 --> 44:12.000
Just...

44:12.200 --> 44:14.290
smart, I guess.

44:14.490 --> 44:17.380
- You are smart.
[chuckles]

44:17.580 --> 44:20.010
I can tell
just by looking at you.

44:20.210 --> 44:24.840
[echoing]
Are your eyes blue or green?

44:25.040 --> 44:28.080
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:28.280 --> 44:29.630
[chuckles]

44:29.830 --> 44:32.020
You're really sweet,
aren't you?

44:32.220 --> 44:35.790
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:35.990 --> 44:37.450
People don't know that
about you, but I do.

44:39.150 --> 44:40.730
And I know you wanna
give me that heart.

44:40.930 --> 44:45.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:45.730 --> 44:47.380
Look who came to our party.

44:48.900 --> 44:50.190
<i>I told you.</i>

44:50.390 --> 44:52.080
That's Tessa Mayfair.

44:52.280 --> 44:53.760
<i>Good work, son.</i>

44:53.960 --> 44:56.550
<i>[tense music]</i>

44:56.750 --> 44:58.570
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

44:58.770 --> 45:01.250
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

45:01.450 --> 45:04.750
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

45:04.950 --> 45:07.360
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

45:07.560 --> 45:09.480
<i>Mi Daemon--</i>

45:10.660 --> 45:12.400
<i>[screams]</i>

45:14.790 --> 45:16.610
<i>On the next episode</i>
<i>of "Mayfair Witches"...</i>

45:16.810 --> 45:18.720
I'm just
looking for Tessa.

45:18.920 --> 45:21.160
Tessa's not
in her room.

45:21.360 --> 45:22.480
Girl: Help!

45:22.680 --> 45:24.180
Cortland:
If he's not with her,

45:24.380 --> 45:26.770
and he's not with you,
where is he?

45:26.970 --> 45:29.970
We have a chance to give proof
of witchcraft.

45:30.170 --> 45:31.470
No more
hiding in the shadows.

45:31.670 --> 45:33.740
Get me outta here!

45:33.930 --> 45:35.610
Woman:
Use the words.

45:35.810 --> 45:38.910
Lasher,
why won't you come to me?

45:44.690 --> 45:47.120
[ Dramatic music plays ]

45:47.320 --> 45:53.780
♪♪

45:53.980 --> 45:55.910
Leave me alone.

45:56.110 --> 45:58.480
Spalding: Rowan
isn't so much conflicted

45:58.680 --> 46:00.610
about whether she wants Lasher
in her life or not

46:00.810 --> 46:02.520
as she is conflicted
about who she is.

46:02.720 --> 46:04.350
Are you gone?

46:04.550 --> 46:06.920
Is she truly a witch?

46:07.120 --> 46:09.360
She knows how she felt
when she killed Carlotta.

46:09.560 --> 46:11.770
She knows that she did that.

46:11.970 --> 46:14.780
Lasher:
I'm always with you.

46:14.980 --> 46:18.020
I'm a part of you --
the part

46:18.220 --> 46:20.130
you pretend not to see
when you look in the mirror.

46:20.330 --> 46:22.280
She's denying who she is,

46:22.480 --> 46:26.110
and Lasher is the instrument
of sort of torment

46:26.310 --> 46:28.900
for saying to her,
"See who you truly are.

46:29.100 --> 46:30.490
I can help you do that."

46:30.690 --> 46:32.230
And part of that
is acknowledging

46:32.430 --> 46:35.060
you are a Mayfair
and we are bound together.

46:35.260 --> 46:37.210
And together, we make
this powerful being,

46:37.410 --> 46:38.690
and you want that."

46:38.890 --> 46:40.690
♪♪

46:40.890 --> 46:42.960
Fire can feel good, too.

46:43.160 --> 46:44.230
See what happens
when you touch it.

46:44.450 --> 46:51.090
♪♪

46:51.290 --> 46:52.660
Parts of what he is offering

46:52.860 --> 46:54.050
are incredibly seductive.

46:54.250 --> 46:56.140
She's torn.

46:56.340 --> 46:58.190
She can't be both
the powerful witch

46:58.390 --> 46:59.890
that Lasher says she is

47:00.090 --> 47:01.630
and also be with Cip.

47:01.830 --> 47:02.980
Ciprien:
What are you doing?

47:03.180 --> 47:04.730
[ Gasps ]

47:04.950 --> 47:07.810
♪♪

47:08.010 --> 47:09.240
Was he here?

47:09.440 --> 47:10.900
What?

47:11.100 --> 47:15.880
♪♪

47:16.080 --> 47:17.290
Alright.

47:17.490 --> 47:19.120
How are you so calm
about this?

47:19.320 --> 47:20.600
That's your mother's heart.

47:20.800 --> 47:22.710
Well, I've seen
a lot of hearts.

47:22.910 --> 47:25.260
Tessa is really
a foil for Rowan.

47:25.460 --> 47:26.830
We have to do something.

47:27.030 --> 47:31.350
It -- This is our family.
<i>Your</i>family.

47:31.550 --> 47:33.660
Tessa is a young woman
in the family.

47:33.860 --> 47:36.470
She wishes
she had more power.

47:36.670 --> 47:38.730
So Tessa is calling on Rowan
and saying,

47:38.930 --> 47:40.580
"You need to take on
the mantle

47:40.780 --> 47:42.670
of what it is to be a Mayfair
and to be a witch.

47:42.870 --> 47:46.110
When they come for us,
we have to stand together

47:46.310 --> 47:47.500
and fight,
or they'll destroy us.

47:47.700 --> 47:49.200
It's what they've been doing
for centuries.

47:49.400 --> 47:52.550
You have real power
right at your fingertips,

47:52.750 --> 47:54.920
and you're doing everything
you can not to use it.

47:55.120 --> 47:57.970
Because there's a price
with him.

47:58.170 --> 47:59.400
And Rowan is saying,
"I don't want that.

47:59.600 --> 48:01.080
I didn't ask for that."

48:01.280 --> 48:03.650
This is not a battle
that I want or would choose.

48:03.850 --> 48:05.340
Just go live your life.

48:05.540 --> 48:07.340
[ Sniffles ]

48:07.540 --> 48:09.000
Maybe you should
go do the same.

48:09.200 --> 48:10.910
That's -- That's just
not possible anymore.

48:11.110 --> 48:12.920
Are you sure?

48:13.120 --> 48:14.970
Or is that something
<i>he</i>wants you to believe?

48:15.190 --> 48:18.680
♪♪

48:18.880 --> 48:20.660
Woman: Rowan Fielding
is here to see you.

48:20.860 --> 48:22.450
Ah.

48:22.650 --> 48:24.410
She goes to Cortland
to say, "Help me out here.

48:24.610 --> 48:25.990
Is there a way
to get rid of him?"

48:26.190 --> 48:27.540
You don't have anything
to be afraid of.

48:27.740 --> 48:30.170
Take the reins.
Tell him what <i>you</i>want.

48:30.370 --> 48:31.500
He's part of you.

48:31.700 --> 48:34.280
I want that part
cut out.

48:34.480 --> 48:38.380
Well, um,
I wish I could help,

48:38.580 --> 48:40.070
but it's impossible.[ China rattling ]

48:40.270 --> 48:41.900
She realizes
in that moment

48:42.100 --> 48:43.750
that Cortland is very unwell.

48:43.950 --> 48:45.730
[ High-pitched tone ]

48:45.930 --> 48:47.020
[ Sighs ]

48:47.210 --> 48:49.010
[ China rattling ]

48:49.230 --> 48:51.080
♪♪

48:51.280 --> 48:53.220
The ALS --

48:53.420 --> 48:55.870
how long since
it was diagnosed?

48:56.070 --> 48:58.220
And I love that Rowan
becomes really a doctor

48:58.420 --> 49:00.480
in this moment,
in this scene with him,

49:00.680 --> 49:02.730
and is very compassionate.

49:02.930 --> 49:05.100
If you want me
to consult with your doctor

49:05.300 --> 49:07.400
and review your treatment plan,
I'd be happy to.

49:07.600 --> 49:10.190
Thank you.

49:10.390 --> 49:11.740
But she also uses it

49:11.930 --> 49:13.850
as a way to convince Cortland
to help her.

49:14.050 --> 49:15.500
If you knew there was
a way for me

49:15.700 --> 49:18.070
to remove the disease
from your body completely,

49:18.270 --> 49:20.770
you would want me to do it,
wouldn't you?

49:20.970 --> 49:22.680
Of course.

49:22.880 --> 49:24.990
Exactly how I feel.

49:25.190 --> 49:27.770
So why won't you help me?

49:27.970 --> 49:29.580
[ Scoffs ]

49:29.780 --> 49:32.230
But, you know,
Cortland is always selfish.

49:32.430 --> 49:34.870
He has other reasons
to do what he's doing.

49:35.070 --> 49:37.000
You're asking me to do
a favor for you, <i>chère.</i>

49:37.200 --> 49:40.520
I mean, surely, you'll
grant me the same courtesy.

49:40.720 --> 49:49.400
♪♪

49:49.600 --> 49:51.670
Ciprien is trying
to understand

49:51.870 --> 49:54.360
Lasher's connection
to the Mayfair women.

49:54.560 --> 49:57.110
And he touches the key
in order to understand it.

49:57.310 --> 49:58.980
It's a memory.
He can't help Suzanne.

49:59.180 --> 50:00.630
It's not like
he's time-traveled.

50:00.830 --> 50:02.070
This is a memory in the past.

50:02.270 --> 50:03.630
But he's able to watch it.

50:03.830 --> 50:05.210
[ Gasps ]

50:05.430 --> 50:07.870
♪♪

50:09.520 --> 50:11.690
So, the origin story
of that necklace

50:11.890 --> 50:14.600
is really that it's
an emblem of her own freedom.

50:14.800 --> 50:16.730
And it connects her
to Lasher.

50:16.930 --> 50:18.260
♪♪

50:18.460 --> 50:20.910
Women: ...Charlotte,

50:21.110 --> 50:22.830
Jeanne-Louise,

50:23.030 --> 50:24.870
Angelique.

50:25.070 --> 50:28.180
Spalding: Rowan is really
going to begin to see

50:28.380 --> 50:30.880
the beauty of the women
of the Mayfair family --

50:31.080 --> 50:32.420
their connection
to each other,

50:32.620 --> 50:34.450
their willingness
to be there for her

50:34.650 --> 50:37.840
to help her through this
transition in this ceremony.

50:38.040 --> 50:41.320
She's really gonna start to feel
like a part of this family.

50:41.520 --> 50:44.410
I love that it's in the act
of trying to get rid of Lasher

50:44.610 --> 50:47.160
that she really finds a place
there in the Mayfairs

50:47.360 --> 50:49.460
and feels connected
to the family

50:49.660 --> 50:50.550
for the first time.

50:50.750 --> 50:52.730
[ Gasping ]

50:52.930 --> 50:54.990
[ Gagging ]

50:55.190 --> 50:56.910
Wait.

50:57.110 --> 50:59.490
[ Gagging ]

50:59.700 --> 51:04.220
♪♪

51:04.420 --> 51:06.180
[ Gasps ]

51:06.380 --> 51:08.050
Spalding: The necklace,
in our contemporary timeline,

51:08.250 --> 51:09.740
can only be in one place
at one time.

51:09.940 --> 51:11.700
And when it comes
out of Rowan's throat

51:11.900 --> 51:13.010
and around the neck of Tessa,

51:13.210 --> 51:15.450
it has disappeared
from the room,

51:15.650 --> 51:17.800
and the Talamasca has
disappeared from Cip's hands.

51:18.000 --> 51:19.360
He's no longer holding it,

51:19.560 --> 51:21.170
which means
he can't release it.

51:21.370 --> 51:23.410
And he is now trapped
in this memory.

51:23.610 --> 51:26.630
You must find your own way
out of the memory.

51:26.830 --> 51:34.430
♪♪
